ld, Ellen 1989. Modaalsusest ja modaalsest predikaadist eesti keeles. – Keel ja \nKirjandus nr 8, lk 468–477. \nUuspõld, Ellen 2001. des- ja mata-vormide kaassõnastumine ja eesti komareeglid. – \nTartu Ülikooli eesti keele õppetooli toimetised 17. Keele kannul. Pühendusteos Mati \nErelti 60. sünnipäevaks 12. märtsil 2001. Toim. Reet Kasik. Tartu: Tartu Ülikooli \nKirjastus, lk 306–321. \nvan der Auwera, Johan, Vladimir A. Plungian 1998. Modality’s Semantic Map. – \nLinguistic Typology, vol. 2, pp. 79–124. \nWatts, Richard J. 1988. A Relevance-theoretic Approach to Commentary Pragmatic \nMarkers: The Case of Actually, Really and Basically. – Acta Linguistica Hungarica, \nvol. 38, No 1–4, pp. 235–260. \nWilkins, David P. 1996. Natural Tendencies of Semantic Change and the Search for \nCognates. – The Comparative Method Reviewed. Regularity and Irregularity in \n 93 \nLanguage Change. Ed. Mark Durie, Malcolm Ross. New York / Oxford: Oxford \nUniversity Press, pp. 264–306. \nWärnsby, Anna 2006. (De)coding Modality. The Case of Must, May, Måste, and Kan. \nLund Studies in English 113. Lund. \nÕS 2006 = Eesti õigekeelsussõnaraamat ÕS 2006. Toim. Tiiu Erelt. Koost. Tiiu Erelt, \nTiina Leemets, Sirje Mäearu, Maire Raadik. Tallinn: Eesti Keele Sihtasutus. \n \n \nEesti kirjakeele korpus; http://www.cl.ut.ee/korpused/kasutajaliides/ \nGoogle; http://www.google.ee \nFitness 2007. Foorum. Vabad teemad. Külastajate küsimused. Küsimus; \nhttp://forums.fitness.ee/lofiversion/index.php/joul/upload/t12881.html \nLapsemure 2009. Foorum. Sport. pmst, teema oleks tüdrukutele (a); \nhttp://www.lapsemure.ee/forum_est/viewtopic.php?f=75&t=19621 \nMercedes-Benz Eesti Klubi 2009. Foorum. Liiklus. Juhtus õnnetus ja nüüd suht \njama seis; http://foorum.clubmb.ee/showthread.php?tid=11970 \nProekspert 2007. Blog. Me tegelt teeme tööd ka veel. \nhttp://people.proekspert.ee/blog/?p=43 \nSoccernet 2006. Foorum. Eesti jalgpall. Madalamad liigad. III Lääs 2006; \nhttp://foorum.soccernet.ee/showthread.php?p=649072  \nSubclub 2004. Foorum. Filmid. Shaun of the Dead; \nhttp://www.subclub.ee/foorum/archive/index.php/t-13910.html \nTasakaalus korpus; http://www.cl.ut.ee/korpused/grammatikaliides/ \n \n \n 94 \n \n \nThe development and use of some of the modal particles \nof written Estonian since the 1890s \n \nSummary \n \nThis Master’s thesis studies some of the modal particles of written Estonian. In the \nterminology of Estonian linguistics, modal particles are modifiers that limit the meaning \nof a sentence by giving modal assessments or forming meaning relations between \ndifferent parts of the text. Modal particles are morphologically invariable, they have \nvery abstract meaning and do not usually change the structure of the sentence. The units \nthat are studied in this present paper are coming from an autosemantic source and they \nare developing gradually into synsemantic words. \n \nThe thesis consists of two chapters. The first chapter provides the theoretical \nbackground of the study: an outline of the theory of grammaticalization is given, the key \nconcepts are introduced, modality in language is characterized and different theoretical \naccounts on modal particles are touched upon. The second chapter is empirical and \npresents the analysis of ten modal particles used in written Estonian since the 1890s. \nThese are praktiliselt, õudselt, loomulikult, põhimõtteliselt, tegelikult, julgelt, vabalt, \ntäpselt, absoluutselt and suhteliselt. The study shows how the use of these particles has \nchanged over the course of time (from the 1890s to 2000s) and touches also upon the \npragmatic aspects of language use: the frequency at which the particles are used and \ntheir evolving functions. \n \nThe validity of a hypothesis proposed by Bybee (2003: 602–605) according to which \nthe probability of grammaticalization is directly related to the frequency at which a \nlexeme is used in language, was then checked. In the context of this study, this meant \ninvestigating whether a correlation could be found between the increasing modal use \n(contra adverbial use, in percents) and the increasing frequency at which these ten \n 95 \nparticles appear in the studied texts. The material selected for analysis originates from \nthe Corpus of Estonian Literary Language and from the Balanced Corpus of Estonian. A \ntotal of 6732 cases where the aforementioned particles appeared were studied. \n \nA separate chapter was dedicated to each modal particle. The main characteristics of a \nspecific particle were given and example sentences were provided. Three figures were \nconstructed for each particles, illustrating their evolving function and use. The first type \nof figure (Fig. 2.1.x.1) gives the absolute number of cases studied per decade and \ndistinguishes between modal (modaalne) and adverbial (adverbiline) use. Cases where \nbased on the information available, no objective distinction between modal and \nadverbial use could be drawn, were marked as emb-kumb. In the second figure (Fig. \n2.1.x.2), the percent-wise comparison of modal/adverbial use is provided. Finally, the \nthird figure (Fig. 2.1.x.3) plots the frequency at which each word appears in the corpus \nas a function of studied decade. In order to avoid very small numbers, frequency per \n100,000 words is used. The second bigger part of the empirical chapter (after describing \neach modal particle separately) is dealing with the extension in studying these modal \nparticles. The connection between the modality and the frequency of the use is shown \nthere. Also the connection between different particles that are analyzed in this theses are \ndescribed. \n \nAll of the particles studied here express a high certainty level of proposition. The \nlanguage user is expressing his or her attitude on whether the proposition is true or not, \naccepting that there is a probability but not being certain. Nevertheless,  each particle \nhas its own specific content that is developing from the lexical meaning. In some cases, \nthe lexical meaning is more dominant (e.g. julgelt) than with the others. The forms that \nare used very often lose their original meaning and become more abstract (e.g. \nloomulikult). While the native speaker still recognizes the full content of the form, the \nresearch showed that the words that are studied here are generally used increasingly as \nmodal particles. Mostly these particles function as sentence adverbials but in some \ncases, only one function (either sentence modifier or phrase modifier) was possible.   \n \n 96 \nThe word forms studied in this thesis agree with the codification of written language: \nDictionaries place these ten words usually as adverbs. However, as has been shown in \nthis thesis, they are developing according to the principles of the grammaticalization \nand therefore, within the time frame of this study, were being used gradually more \nfrequently as modal particles. Their original function as adverbs is eroding and they will \nincreasingly function only as sentence modifiers. \n \n 97 \n \n \nLisad \n \nLisa 1. Analüüsil kasutatud ilukirjanduslikud materjalid alates aastast 2000 \nAutor Pealkiri Sõnu Aasta \nAarne Biin Peegelleitnandid  50756 2001 \nAarne Ruben Vares-Barbaruse valitsus 50289 2001 \nAarne Ruben Randevuude rajad on rammetult rohtund 2574 2003 \nAarne Ruben Elajas trepi eesastmel 68508 2004 \nAidi Vallik Kuidas elad, Ann? Katkendid 4991 2000 \nAndre Trinity Unenägude jumal 8440 2000 \nAndre Trinity Glorie igavene kohalolek 12581 2001 \nAndrus \nKivirähk \nTormine rand, Püha graal, Ivan Orava mälestused, \nKotkas 25105 2005 \nAndrus \nVanapa Vanapagana teine tosin 27243 2002 \nAnton Nigov Harjutused 82116 2002 \nArne Ruben Volta annab kaeblikku vilet 85424 2001 \nArno Kasemaa Maa ja armastus 110709 2000 \nArno Kasemaa Metsad kõnelevad 76694 2001 \nArvo Uustalu Mart ja Toivo 2306 2003 \nArvo Uustalu Habemeajaja 10612 2009 \nArvo Valton Kahekõned kohvikutes 32129 